<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4576857>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 8. Habitats of Hydroscapha in Taiwan and Hong Kong. A–C, mass occurrence of H. takahashii in Taiwan, Heshe: A, detail of living beetles in algal mat at wet concrete wall; B, wet concrete wall with algae at sides of Zhenyoulanxi river; C, view of algal mat showing numerous adults and larvae. D, E, type locality of H. shuihau, new species, in Hong Kong: D, general view of marsh below Shui Hui village, with small seeps at concrete trail; E, microhabitat at sides of concrete trail from where beetles were collected; F, algal mats at side of a small river in Taiwan: Wufeng, with mass occurrence of H. takahashii." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4576857/files/figure.png" .

